Notes 

1.npm init --> to initialise package.json 
2.npm install twit --save // save will add it to package.json
3. in package.json file if you add start: node bot.js , then whenever you give command npm start , then a bot.js file gets loaded .
4. to access a package  --> var twit = require ('twit')
5. var config = require(./config)
   var t =new twit(config);// creates a new object with contents of config file.